Biography Diana Shpak

Born 27/01/1997

. Winner of the prize for best female image in 2003 at the XIII Moscow International Advertising Festival

. Star Advertising

. Acting life of Diana Shpak started in three years, when her mother's daughter in classified photos actor's agency

. Almost immediately, the girl began to shoot in advertising - first for 'Kinder-surprise', and then in advertising juice 'Orchard', where Diana appears as a 'purple plums, ripe garden'.

. Diana was glorified as advertising clip juice 'My Family', where she made her crown phrase 'And you and pour away! "

. For this work, girl got a prize for best female image in 2003 at the XIII Moscow International Advertising Festival.

Movies

Thanks to advances in advertising on Diana drew the attention of filmmakers. In 2005 she starred in the feature film 'Forest Princess', produced by Alexander Basov, and Teimuraz Esadze. In the same year, Diana, a great contest, was approved for the role of Liza Orlova, daughter of the protagonist (played by Tatyana Dogileva) in the series 'Lyuba, Children and plant'.

The role of Diana manages to perfectly thanks largely mum. However, they understand each episode, rehearse cues. Young actress to his work is seriously. 'In his 8 years of Diana a true professional, - says Tatiana Dogileva. - There are times when shooting are tightened until midnight, and then she, of course, complains: "I'll fall down from exhaustion," but, nevertheless, goes to the site and doing what the director asks. "

. Diana admits that as yet does not know whether it will in the future actress

. In the meantime, she has easy. Lessons in school, piano lessons and, of course, the shooting, which sometimes go on for 10 - 12 hours a day. But Diana did not complain, and, probably, so it all possible.

Filmography:

2005 Forest Princess

2005 Luba, children and the plant - series
